abstract: Hubbard, Ohio, Nov. 13. -- James Mahany, John Richards, and Martin Rosteth were butchering pigs this morning. Mahany and Rosteth quarreled, and Rosteth whipped Mahany. Richards is likely to die, but he refuses to make a complaint, saying Mahany did not intend to shoot him.

Neighbors extinguished the flames, but Mrs. Levy was so badly injured that she died at St. Francis's Hospital four hours later.
